(1-\cos\alpha)^2 + \sin^2\alpha = d^2 
2+2\cos\alpha+\frac{\cos2\alpha}{2}-\frac{\sin\alpha}{2} = d^2
(1-\cos(\alpha))^2+\sin^2(\alpha)=d^2
1-2\cos(\alpha)+\cos^2(\alpha)+\sin^2(\alpha)=d^2
1-2\cos(\alpha)+1=d^2
2-2\cos(\alpha)=d^2
\cos(\alpha)=1-\frac{d^2}{2}
\alpha=\cos^{-1}\left(1-\frac{d^2}{2}\right)
\sin^2 \alpha
\cos^2 \alpha
\sin^2 \alpha + \cos^2 \alpha = 1
\left( 1-\cos \alpha \right)^2 + \sin ^2 \alpha = 1 - 2 \cos \alpha + \cos^2 \alpha + \sin^2 \alpha
\cos^2 \alpha + \sin^2 \alpha = 1
\sin^{2}x = 1-\cos^{2}{x}
 \frac{d^{2}}{4} =\sin^{2}\frac{x}{2} \Longrightarrow \sin\frac{x}{2} = \pm\frac{d}{2}
